cs.LG, cs.IT, cs.AI, cs.CR, cs.DS 

This paper deals with objective evaluation of classifications using information-theoretic measures, which is a topic that falls under the broad category of machine learning and data analysis. Specifically, the paper proposes a set of normalized ITMs for classification assessment, which is a subfield of machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.IT (Information Theory), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
